O'FALLON CHAMBER OF COMMERCE: ADC is proud to announce the 2018 recipients of its Defense Community Awards. Winners will be recognized during the 2018 Defense Communities National Summit, June 18-20, in Washington, D.C.

Business

By Press release submission | May 11, 2018

AddThis Sharing Sidebar
Share to Facebook
, Number of shares
Share to TwitterShare to Reddit
, Number of shares
More AddThis Share options
, Number of shares
Hide
Show


O'Fallon Chamber of Commerce issued the following announcement on May 7.

We are very pleased to report that St. Clair County Board Chairman Mark A. Kern has been selected to receive the prestigious “Community Leadership Award” from the Association of Defense Communities (ADC). This will be presented to Mark at the annual ADC National Summit this coming June 18-20 in Washington, DC.

My office nominated Mark for this award and he is being honored for his long-time support of Scott AFB (the major points in his selection are attached). While ADC will issue a formal press release later as the event nears in June, they did announce it briefly in today’s “On-Base” newsletter. I have also attached a copy of today’s story.

Mark and the other award recipients will also be featured in the American Defense Communities magazine and they will be recognized throughout the Summit. The magazine will be published in the very near future.

ADC will take plenty of photos and a video when Mark receives the award on stage in June, so watch for those. Feel free to drop Mark a congratulatory note at mkern@co.st-clair.il.us

Note: We are longtime ADC members and also belonged to its predecessor-the National Association of Installation Developers (NAID).

ADC: https://www.defensecommunities.org/ and their National Defense Summit: https://www.adcsummit.org/

Original source can be found here.
